{
  "texts": [
    "In case of NER, the hidden states could represent different entities and the observable symbols are the words in the text [38].HMM have transition and emission probabilities that determine the likelihood of moving from one entity to another and the likelihood of observing a particular word of observing a particular word occurring in a specific entity type.Mathematically, it is expressed as:Let, 𝑆 = {𝑠 1, 𝑠 2, 𝑠 3, ------𝑠 𝑛 } be the set of hidden states i.e represent different entity labels and, 𝑂 = {𝑜 1, 𝑜 2, 𝑠 3, ------𝑜 𝑛 } be the set of observations (words) in the input sequence.",
    "The probability of starting in state 𝑠 𝑖:Π 𝑖 = 𝑃( 𝑞 1 = 𝑠 𝑖)(1)The probability of transitioning from state 𝑠 𝑖 to 𝑠 𝑗:𝑎 𝑖𝑗 = 𝑃(𝑞 𝑡+1 = 𝑠 𝑗 / 𝑞 𝑡 = 𝑠 𝑖)(2)The probability of observing word 𝑜 𝑡 when in state 𝑠 𝑗 is represented as:𝑏 𝑗 (𝑜 𝑡) = 𝑃(𝑜 𝑡 / 𝑞 𝑡 = 𝑠 𝑗)(3) (b) Conditional Random FieldIt is a type of statistical model used for sequence labelling task like NER.",
    "CRFs work by defining a set of features that capture the characteristics of each word and then it assigns weight to these features based on a training dataset [31], [43], [108].",
    "During, inference, given a sequence of words, the CRF calculates the probability of all possible NER tags using defined features and corresponding weighs [38].",
    "The sequence having high probability will be selected."
  ]
}